   "source": [
    ".. index:: Equations; Mean Curvature Flow\n",
    "\n",
    ".. index:: Equations; Surface PDE\n",
    "\n",
    ".. index:: Methods; Moving domains\n",
    "\n",
    "# Moving surface grid: flow under mean curvature\n",
    "\n",
    "This example uses a\n",
    "[moving grid](gridviews_and_adaptivity.rst#Evolving-Domains).\n",
    "\n",
    "Mean curvature flow is a specific example of a geometric evolution\n",
    "equation where the evolution is governed by the mean curvature $H$.\n",
    "One real-life example of this is in how soap films change over time,\n",
    "although it can also be applied to image processing (e.g.\n",
    "<cite data-cite=\"Malladi\"></cite>).\n",
    "Assume we can define a reference surface $\\Gamma_0$ such that\n",
    "we can write the evolving surface $\\Gamma(t)$ in the form\n",
    "\\begin{gather*}\n",
    "\\Gamma(t) = X(t,\\Gamma_0).\n",
    "\\end{gather*}\n",
    "It is now possible to show that the vector valued function $X=X(t,x)$\n",
    "with $x\\in\\Gamma_0$ satisfies\n",
    "\\begin{gather*}\n",
    "\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial_t}X = - H(X)\\nu(X),\n",
    "\\end{gather*}\n",
    "where $H$ is the mean curvature of $\\Gamma_t$ and $\\nu$ is its outward pointing normal.\n",
    "\n",
    "We will solve this using a finite element approach based on the\n",
    "following time discrete approximation from\n",
    "<cite data-cite=\"Charlie\"></cite>\n",
    "(with a $\\theta$-scheme applied).\n",
    "\\begin{align*}\n",
    "\\int_{\\Gamma^n} \\big( U^{n+1} - {\\rm id}\\big) \\cdot \\varphi +\n",
    "\\tau \\int_{\\Gamma^n} \\big(\n",
    "\\theta\\nabla_{\\Gamma^n} U^{n+1} + (1-\\theta) I \\big)\n",
    "\\colon\\nabla_{\\Gamma^n}\\varphi\n",
    "=0.\n",
    "\\end{align*}\n",
    "Here $U^n$ parametrizes $\\Gamma(t^{n+1})$ over\n",
    "$\\Gamma^n:=\\Gamma(t^{n})$, $I$ is the identity matrix, $\\tau$ is the\n",
    "time step and $\\theta\\in[0,1]$ is a discretization parameter.\n",
    "<img src=\"mcf.gif\" style=\"height:228px;\">"
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "from ufl import *\n",
    "from dune.ufl import Constant, DirichletBC\n",
    "import dune.ufl\n",
    "import dune.geometry as geometry\n",
    "import dune.fem as fem\n",
    "from dune.fem.plotting import plotPointData as plot\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as pyplot"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1237e5f6",
   "metadata": {
    "lines_to_next_cell": 2
   },
   "source": [
    "set up polynomial order and radius of reference surface"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "931b58e3",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2025-11-29T18:53:02.147460Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2025-11-29T18:53:02.147189Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2025-11-29T18:53:02.150350Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2025-11-29T18:53:02.149572Z"
    },
    "lines_to_next_cell": 2
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "order = 2\n",
    "R0 = 2."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bb4c133e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    ".. index: Grid construction; Dune Grid Format file (`DGF`_)\n",
    "\n",
    "We begin by setting up reference domain $\\Gamma_0$ (```grid```)\n",
    "([a sphere](sphere.dgf)), and the space on $\\Gamma_0$ that describes $\\Gamma(t)$ (```space```).\n",
    "From this we interpolate the non-spherical initial surface ```positions```, and, then reconstruct ```space``` for the discrete solution on $\\Gamma(t)$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "f42894f7",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2025-11-29T18:53:02.152151Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2025-11-29T18:53:02.151981Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2025-11-29T18:53:03.187682Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2025-11-29T18:53:03.186691Z"
    },
    "lines_to_next_cell": 2
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from dune.fem.view import geometryGridView\n",
    "from dune.fem.space import lagrange as solutionSpace\n",
    "from dune.alugrid import aluConformGrid as leafGridView\n",
    "gridView = leafGridView(\"sphere.dgf\", dimgrid=2, dimworld=3)\n",
    "space = solutionSpace(gridView, dimRange=gridView.dimWorld, order=order)\n",
    "u = TrialFunction(space)\n",
    "v = TestFunction(space)\n",
    "x = SpatialCoordinate(space)\n",
    "# positions = space.interpolate(x * (1 + 0.5*sin(2*pi*x[0]*x[1])* cos(pi*x[2])), name=\"position\")\n",
    "positions = space.interpolate(x * (1 + 0.5*sin(2*pi*(x[0]+x[1]))*cos(0.25*pi*x[2])), name=\"position\")\n",
    "surface = geometryGridView(positions)\n",
    "space = solutionSpace(surface, dimRange=surface.dimWorld, order=order)\n",
    "solution = space.interpolate(x, name=\"solution\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4647be38",
   "metadata": {
    "lines_to_next_cell": 2
   },
   "source": [
    "We set up the theta scheme with $\\theta = 0.5$ (Crank-Nicolson)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "d7022749",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2025-11-29T18:53:03.189587Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2025-11-29T18:53:03.189306Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2025-11-29T18:53:03.263833Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2025-11-29T18:53:03.262948Z"
    },
    "lines_to_next_cell": 2
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from dune.fem.scheme import galerkin as solutionScheme\n",
    "theta = 0.5\n",
    "I = Identity(3)\n",
    "dt = Constant(0, \"dt\")\n",
    "\n",
    "a = (inner(u - x, v) + dt * inner(theta*grad(u) + (1 - theta)*I, grad(v))) * dx\n",
    "scheme = solutionScheme(a == 0, space, solver=\"cg\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f3c58c5e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we solve the scheme in time. We first set up the initial time variables, then we plot the initial figure's mesh, and finally we begin the loop, updating ```positions``` on each step and plotting the results side-by-side."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "6e1681e5",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2025-11-29T18:53:03.265564Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2025-11-29T18:53:03.265382Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2025-11-29T18:53:03.953865Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2025-11-29T18:53:03.952842Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 500x500 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "count = 0\n",
    "t = 0.\n",
    "end_time = 0.05\n",
    "dt.value = 0.005\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = pyplot.figure(figsize=(10, 10))\n",
    "plot(solution, figure=(fig, 131+count%3), colorbar=False,\n",
    "     gridLines=\"\", triplot=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "while t < end_time:\n",
    "    scheme.solve(target=solution)\n",
    "    t += scheme.model.dt\n",
    "    count += 1\n",
    "    positions.assign(solution)\n",
    "    if count % 4 == 0:\n",
    "        plot(solution, figure=(fig, 131+count%3), colorbar=False,\n",
    "             gridLines=\"\", triplot=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f4a11f66",
   "metadata": {
    "lines_to_next_cell": 0
   },
   "source": [
    "By choosing an initial surface with boundary we can solve the [soap film](soap.dgf)\n",
    "problem, i.e., compute the surface of minimum curvature:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "fb8febd0",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2025-11-29T18:53:03.955546Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2025-11-29T18:53:03.955369Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2025-11-29T18:53:04.137434Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2025-11-29T18:53:04.136514Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pyplot.close('all')\n",
    "referenceView = leafGridView(\"soap.dgf\", dimgrid=2, dimworld=3)\n",
    "referenceView.hierarchicalGrid.globalRefine(8)\n",
    "space = solutionSpace(referenceView, dimRange=referenceView.dimWorld,\n",
    "        order=order)\n",
    "\n",
    "# setup deformed surface\n",
    "x         = SpatialCoordinate(space)\n",
    "# note that 'positions' also deforms the boundary which will then be fixed\n",
    "# during the evolution by the chosen boundary conditions:\n",
    "positions = space.interpolate(x * (1 + 0.5*sin(2*pi*(x[0]+x[1]))*cos(0.25*pi*x[2])), name=\"position\")\n",
    "gridView  = geometryGridView(positions)\n",
    "space     = solutionSpace(gridView, dimRange=gridView.dimWorld, order=order)\n",
    "\n",
    "u     = TrialFunction(space)\n",
    "phi   = TestFunction(space)\n",
    "dt    = Constant(0.01, \"timeStep\")\n",
    "t     = Constant(0.0, \"time\")\n",
    "endTime      = 0.4\n",
    "saveInterval = 0.1\n",
    "\n",
    "# define storage for discrete solutions\n",
    "uh     = space.interpolate(x, name=\"uh\")\n",
    "uh_old = uh.copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# problem definition\n",
    "\n",
    "# space form\n",
    "xForm = inner(grad(u), grad(phi)) * dx\n",
    "\n",
    "# add time discretization\n",
    "form = dot(u - uh_old, phi) * dx + dt * xForm\n",
    "\n",
    "# define Dirichlet boundary conditions - freezing the boundary\n",
    "bc = DirichletBC(space,x)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "096d61e2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Choosing solver parameters is done by passing a dictionary when constructing\n",
    "the scheme."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "567ce69f",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2025-11-29T18:53:04.139190Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2025-11-29T18:53:04.139010Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2025-11-29T18:53:04.217151Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2025-11-29T18:53:04.216030Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "solverParameters =\\\n",
    "       {\"nonlinear.tolerance\": 1e-9,\n",
    "        \"linear.tolerance\": 1e-11,\n",
    "        \"linear.preconditioning.method\": \"jacobi\",\n",
    "        \"nonlinear.verbose\": False,\n",
    "        \"linear.preconditioning.iteration\": 3}\n",
    "# setup scheme\n",
    "scheme = solutionScheme([form == 0, bc], space, solver=\"cg\",\n",
    "                        parameters=solverParameters)\n",
    "\n",
    "nextSaveTime = saveInterval\n",
    "count = 0"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6015c25b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

    "fig = pyplot.figure(figsize=(50, 10))\n",
    "plot(solution, figure=(fig, 151+count), colorbar=False,\n",
    "     gridLines=\"\", triplot=True)\n",
    "while t.value < endTime:\n",
    "    uh_old.assign(uh)\n",
    "    info = scheme.solve(target=uh)\n",
    "    t.value += dt.value\n",
    "\n",
    "    positions.assign(uh)\n",
    "\n",
    "    if t.value >= nextSaveTime or t.value >= endTime:\n",
    "        nextSaveTime += saveInterval\n",
    "        count += 1\n",
    "        plot(uh, figure=(fig, 151+count), colorbar=False,\n",
    "             gridLines=\"\", triplot=True)\n",
    "plot3d(uh,2)"
